History is not some random event it IS most of the time a conspiracy. A conspiracy is simply an agreement that is done in secret or by deliberate deception about certain events, nothing more. His childlike silliness in most of his comments and descriptions is exactly why conspiracies work: ignorance by idiots. Getting back to this book, Griffin's writing is so clear and concise and well sourced that it's a pleasure and a duty of intelligent people to consider it
